                <h1 id="label-Patterns">Patterns<span><a href="#label-Patterns">&para;</a> <a href="#documentation">&uarr;</a></span></h1>

                <p>This project began because I wanted to help some of the people at work
                learn Ruby, and I decided I could turn those lessons into a class on design
                patterns, implementation, and testing. All of the patterns implemented here
                will be fully rdoc&#39;d and will contain a complete set of tests using
                Rspec.</p>

                <h2 id="label-Installation">Installation<span><a href="#label-Installation">&para;</a> <a href="#documentation">&uarr;</a></span></h2>

                <p>Add this line to your application&#39;s Gemfile:</p>

                <pre class="ruby"><span class="ruby-identifier">gem</span> <span class="ruby-string">&#39;Patterns&#39;</span></pre>

                <p>And then execute:</p>

                <pre>$ bundle</pre>

                <p>Or install it yourself as:</p>

                <pre>$ gem install DesignPatterns</pre>
